# Animation Standards

The portfolio should feel premium, smooth and responsive.

Animations must improve usability and storytelling.

Never animate purely for decoration.

## Smooth Scrolling

Use Lenis for smooth scrolling.

### Requirements

- One global Lenis instance.
- Do not create multiple instances.
- Integrate with `requestAnimationFrame`.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Smooth scrolling should not interfere with accessibility.
- Anchor links should scroll smoothly.
- Preserve browser history.

## Motion

Use Framer Motion for:

- Component entrance
- Hover effects
- Buttons
- Cards
- Navbar
- Theme transitions
- Modal animations

## GSAP

Use GSAP only for:

- ScrollTrigger
- Sticky sections
- Pinned storytelling
- SVG line drawing
- Hero transitions

Never use GSAP for simple fades or hover effects.

## CSS

- Prefer CSS transitions whenever possible.
- Use Framer Motion only when state-driven animation is required.
- Avoid unnecessary JavaScript animations.

## Performance

Animations should maintain 60 FPS.

- Avoid layout thrashing.
- Prefer `transform` and `opacity`.

### Avoid animating

- `width`
- `height`
- `top`
- `left`

### Animate only

- `opacity`
- `transform`
- `filter` (sparingly)

## Accessibility

- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Provide non-animated fallbacks.
- Animations must never block interaction.

## Timing

| Context | Duration |
|---------|----------|
| Hover | 200ms |
| Page Transition | 300ms |
| Scroll Reveal | 500ms |
| Theme Change | 300ms |

- Use `ease-out` by default.
- Avoid spring animations unless they improve usability.

## Folder Structure

Organize animation code from day one.

```
src/
├── components/
├── hooks/
│   ├── use-lenis.ts
│   ├── use-scroll-progress.ts
│   ├── use-parallax.ts
│   └── use-prefers-reduced-motion.ts
├── animations/
│   ├── fade.ts
│   ├── stagger.ts
│   ├── reveal.ts
│   ├── page.ts
│   ├── cards.ts
│   ├── navbar.ts
│   └── hero.ts
├── lib/
│   └── lenis.ts
└── providers/
    └── smooth-scroll-provider.tsx
```

- `lib/lenis.ts` — single Lenis instance factory/config.
- `providers/smooth-scroll-provider.tsx` — global Lenis context wrapper.
- `animations/` — reusable Framer Motion variants and GSAP timelines.
- `hooks/` — scroll and motion utilities consumed by components.

## Section Effects

### Hero

- Staggered text reveal
- CTA fade-up
- Background grid drift
- Scroll indicator

### Navbar

- Blur on scroll
- Active link indicator
- Progress bar

### Metrics

- Count-up once
- Fade-up
- Border highlight on hover

### Featured Projects

- Sticky storytelling
- Image reveal
- Annotation lines
- Slight parallax

### Timeline

- Line drawing
- Card reveal
- Active node scaling

### Contact

- Gentle gradient movement
- Button hover
- Social icon lift

## Effects to Avoid with Lenis

Lenis already changes the feel of scrolling. Avoid:

- Heavy parallax everywhere
- Mouse-following blobs
- Scroll-jacking
- Infinite floating cards
- Full-page skew effects
- Horizontal scrolling sections (unless there is a compelling reason)

These often make a portfolio feel more like a demo than a polished product.

## Lenis + GSAP Integration

Integrate Lenis and GSAP properly — do not run them independently.

- Let Lenis drive the scroll updates that ScrollTrigger listens to.
- Keeps pinned sections, progress indicators, and animations synchronized.
- Avoids jitter or desynchronization when both systems try to control scrolling separately.
